## Description {#details}

A <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/linkgraph">LinkGraph</a> pass that adds missing FDE-to-CIE, FDE-to-PC and FDE-to-LSDA edges.

### EHFrameEdgeFixer() {#ac454f1b37ee399349874df2e004fbce3}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>llvm::jitlink::EHFrameEdgeFixer::EHFrameEdgeFixer (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> EHFrameSectionName, unsigned PointerSize, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/edge/#af18145da213e6c4033b368d657e80baa">Edge::Kind</a> Pointer32, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/edge/#af18145da213e6c4033b368d657e80baa">Edge::Kind</a> Pointer64, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/edge/#af18145da213e6c4033b368d657e80baa">Edge::Kind</a> Delta32, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/edge/#af18145da213e6c4033b368d657e80baa">Edge::Kind</a> Delta64, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/edge/#af18145da213e6c4033b368d657e80baa">Edge::Kind</a> NegDelta32)</>}>
Create an eh-frame edge fixer.

Adds edges for implicit relocations on platforms where these are used (e.g. MachO/x86-64).

If a given edge-kind is not supported on the target architecture then <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/edge/#aa21629cef4aed37ffc47ef8681c46a99a5ac566a913119de4e29b016756ce6e9f">Edge::Invalid</a> should be used.
